## Functions

### decode() {#af862e87da17b134b4d6875d052bbbc88}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static llvm::Expected&lt; InlineInfo &gt; decode (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dataextractor">DataExtractor</a> &amp; Data, uint64&#95;t &amp; Offset, uint64&#95;t BaseAddr)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Decode an <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> in Data at the specified offset.

A local helper function to decode <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> objects. This function is called recursively when parsing child <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> objects.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Data">The data extractor to decode from.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Offset">The offset within <em>Data</em> to decode from.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="BaseAddr">The base address to use when decoding address ranges.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
An <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> or an error describing the issue that was encountered during decoding.
</SectionUser>

### lookup() {#a5db99f4b7f8744e0b1c8b50dba8ec5a2}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool lookup (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/gsym/gsymreader">GsymReader</a> &amp; GR, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dataextractor">DataExtractor</a> &amp; Data, uint64&#95;t &amp; Offset, uint64&#95;t BaseAddr, uint64&#95;t Addr, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/gsym/#af56cdce2bbbfcdafb057bce7c90bf419">SourceLocations</a> &amp; SrcLocs, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">llvm::Error</a> &amp; Err)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
A Lookup helper functions.

Used during the InlineInfo::lookup() call to quickly only parse an <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> object if the address falls within this object. This avoids allocations by not appending child <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> objects to the InlineInfo::Children array and also skips any <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> objects that do not contain the address we are looking up.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Data">The binary stream to read the data from.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Offset">The byte offset within <em>Data</em>.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="BaseAddr">The address that the relative address range offsets are relative to.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

Definition at line <a href="#l00108">108</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/gsym/inlineinfo-cpp">InlineInfo.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### skip() {#ac05a52a6d1ce8dda0f50063c9c22e5f4}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool skip (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dataextractor">DataExtractor</a> &amp; Data, uint64&#95;t &amp; Offset, bool SkippedRanges)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Skip an <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> object in the specified data at the specified offset.

Used during the InlineInfo::lookup() call to quickly skip child <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> objects where the addres ranges isn&#39;t contained in the <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> object or its children. This avoids allocations by not appending child <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/inlineinfo">InlineInfo</a> objects to the InlineInfo::Children array.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Data">The binary stream to read the data from.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Offset">The byte offset within <em>Data</em>.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="SkippedRanges">If true, address ranges have already been skipped.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

Definition at line <a href="#l00076">76</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/gsym/inlineinfo-cpp">InlineInfo.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>
